                            <comment id="234149" author="artem_blagodarenko" created="Mon, 1 Oct 2018 08:29:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Andreas gave good reason to not delete extents support on OSS. I am closing this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="189624" author="adilger" created="Fri, 24 Mar 2017 20:39:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The main question isn&apos;t whether we format new filesystems with extents, but rather whether any filesystems exist that have block-mapped files for some reason?  For example, we format the MDT without extents, and it has regular files (llog and OI files).  Also, with Data-on-MDT the MDT will start doing bulk IO, so I think this patch would break the OSD code. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
